			<ns0:name>robertm@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/robertm@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">When we enable nacl inside chrome we also enable the use
of the trusted TC (including irt builds and tests).

The use of the untrusted TC in the chrome build is a heavy dependency and currently broken for ARM -- until we manage to hook up the PNaCl TC.

To allow for some progress on the ARM chrome build we should control the use of the untrusted TC via another flag, e.g. &amp;quot;disable_nacl_untrusted_components&amp;quot;.

This feature should allow us to setup a lightweight arm bot that ensures that at least all the main components can be build, thought it
would not run any tests.

It might also be useful for chrome developers who otherwise would just
disable_nacl=1 to have more fine grained control when running into nacl related build problems.

 
